<paragraph blockId="226.[151,1437,1782,2040]" pageId="226" pageNumber="227">
<emphasis box="[207,450,1899,1923]" italics="true" pageId="226" pageNumber="227">Diagnostic characters</emphasis>
: The species differs from other members of the genus except 
<taxonomicName authority="Ferrington Jr &amp; Saether, 2011" authorityName="Ferrington Jr &amp; Saether" authorityYear="2011" box="[1134,1248,1899,1923]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Pseudosmittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="226" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palpina" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1134,1248,1899,1923]" italics="true" pageId="226" pageNumber="227">P. palpina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1257,1319,1899,1923]" pageId="226" pageNumber="227">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1257,1319,1899,1923]" pageId="226" pageNumber="227" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by having reduced palpomeres. It differs from the other two species in the group by having no postcubital fork, only slightly arched transverse sternapodeme and curved gonostylus.
</paragraph>
